hooks/cinder_hooks.py.message:
The 'fix' is to use a feature of pausable_restart_on_change() (which is what's actually been used), which takes callables.  Disclaimer -- I wrote the change!  Then you can define a function for the restart_funcs that only gets evaluated when the hook is used rather than at load time:

    def restart_funcs_f():
        restart_funcs = {}
        if run_in_apache('cinder-api'):
            restart_funcs['apache2'] = restart_pid_check


    @restart_on_change(restart_map, stopstart=True,
                       restart_functions=restart_funcs_f)
    def config_changed(....)

Also, if pausable_restart_on_change is used the restart_map and restart_funcs can be passed as functions rather than the results of the functions i.e.

    @pausable_restart_on_change(restart_map, ...,
                                restart_functions=restart_funcs)
    def function(...)

i.e. don't call the functions restart_map(), but just pass the function name (actually the reference to the function).  This will make it lazy and so won't run it at load time.

